{
  "texts": [
    "However, these methods often involved manual intervention and provided only semiautomated segmentation.To address these limitations, researchers used recent advances in deep learning and proposed fully automated segmentation methods for dental models.",
    "For example, Xu et al. [5] introduced a framework that converts dental models into geometric features, which are then transformed into 2D images.",
    "These images are then used to train CNNs to classify mesh faces.",
    "The network was integrated into a complex pipeline that involved multiple pre-and post-processing steps.",
    "Another approach presented by Tian et al. [6] utilized octree partitioning to voxelize the dental model."
  ]
}